@demps2k9 wrote:

It’s in clickingMost and you need to find out the button ID first.

To find it out click on your teleport and then look at your CMD if you’re using localhost/127.0.0.1.

Then search that ID in your clickingMost.java.

item.title: Need help pleasee
item.dc:creator: @Skiire Skiire
item.description:
@Skiire wrote:

Depending on the source it could be in any file. Classes are supposed to be named and contain the information you’re looking for, however the client class renamed to alkjsg does the same functions, it’s just not following conventions. These types of questions are redundant and quite simply fixed with a little effort on your part.

Get a program capable of a recursive file search such as Eclipse or even a Z-File Searcher… I highly recommend Eclipse though. Then just search the coordinate and it will go through every file until it finds/doesn’t find that string. This will save you countless hours waiting on replies to these simplistic questions.
